data.enText: the feeling of not being able to believe sth
He stared at me in disbelief .

data.chText: 要欣赏这部电影就得暂且相信那甚至不可能发生的事。
data.enText: To enjoy the movie you have to suspend your disbelief (= pretend to believe sth, even if it seems very unlikely) .

ex.chText: 不信上帝是他的原则之一。
ex.enText: The unbelief in God is one of his principles.

ex.chText: 那部法典中提到的罪孽之一就是无信仰。
ex.enText: One sin mentioned in that code is unbelief.

synonyms.bx: 主要用于宗教信仰方面。

ex.chText: 他站在门口，疑惑地盯着我看。
ex.enText: He stood at the door, staring at me in disbelief.

ex.chText: 这不同于简单的怀疑或拒绝。
ex.enText: This is not the same thing as simple disbelief or rejection.

synonyms.bx: 指觉得某事物不真实或并不存在。

tr: doubt about the truth of something

value.def: Disbelief is not believing that something is true or real.

example.ex: She looked at him in disbelief.

trans: 怀疑；怀疑地；不相信；不相信地；怀疑的
悬置疑问；暂时让自己相信虚构的事物
